Testing Rules
What to Test (Prioritised)

PHP Repository methods — all SQL queries, filter combinations, soft delete, boolean casting
PHP API response envelopes — correct shape, correct status codes
TypeScript type guards — isApiSuccess(), enum validators
React hooks — useKanbanReorder, useQuickLog, useCanvasDrag
Utility functions — date formatting, fractional order calculation, prompt builder

What NOT to Test

Tailwind class names
Framer Motion animation values
Zustand store shape (covered by TypeScript)
External API responses (mock them, don't test the mocks)

PHP Testing (PHPUnit)

Test file mirrors source: src/Repositories/TaskRepository.php → tests/Repositories/TaskRepositoryTest.php
Use in-memory SQLite (:memory:) — run schema before each test, wipe after
Never test via HTTP in unit tests — test Repository and Service classes directly
Mock external services (AnthropicService, GoogleAuthService) with PHPUnit mocks

TypeScript Testing (Vitest)

Co-locate tests: hooks/useTasks.test.ts next to hooks/useTasks.ts
Mock TanStack Query with @tanstack/react-query test utilities
Mock Axios with vi.mock('../api/client')
Component tests use @testing-library/react — test behaviour not implementation

Test Data Factories
PHP:
php// tests/Factories/TaskFactory.php
TaskFactory::make(['status' => 'in_progress', 'project_id' => 1])
TaskFactory::makeMany(5, ['status' => 'backlog'])
TypeScript:
ts// tests/factories/task.ts
export const makeTask = (overrides: Partial<Task> = {}): Task => ({
  id: 1, title: 'Test task', status: 'backlog', priority: 2, ...overrides
})
